<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Collier</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-29"><hi rend="italic">June 29,
                                1906</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 55.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 109, of the 8th instant, reporting concerning the festivities
                            attending the wedding of His Majesty the King.</p>
                        <p>You will make suitable expression of this Government’s thanks for the
                            courtesies paid to the special ambassador and suite, and express
                            appreciation of the consideration shown by Señor Don Jaime de Ojeda, who
                            acted as aid and escort to the ambassador.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>